## Example 3 — Determine Whether to Use Law of Sines or Law of Cosines

Classify each problem and state which law to use.

**(a)** $\angle A = 50°$, $\angle B = 70°$, $a = 15$ (find $b$)

Two angles and a non-included side (AAS). **Use the Law of Sines.**

**(b)** $a = 8$, $b = 13$, $\angle C = 110°$ (find $c$)

Two sides and the included angle (SAS). **Use the Law of Cosines.**

**(c)** $a = 5$, $b = 9$, $c = 11$ (find all angles)

Three sides (SSS). **Use the Law of Cosines.**

**(d)** $a = 10$, $\angle A = 35°$, $\angle C = 80°$ (find $c$)

Two angles and a non-included side (AAS). **Use the Law of Sines.**

**(e)** $a = 7$, $c = 12$, $\angle B = 40°$ (find $b$)

Two sides and the included angle (SAS). **Use the Law of Cosines.**

✅ Answer: Use the Law of Sines for AAS/ASA; use the Law of Cosines for SAS or SSS.

